────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DATA NOTICE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The data files distributed with this repository (rijal_database_merged.json,
alf_rajul_database.json, allBooks.json, mufid_statuses.json, and related
indices) are derived from classical and modern public Islamic scholarship:

  - al-Mufīd min Muʿjam Rijāl al-Ḥadīth — Muḥammad al-Jawāhirī
    (a summary of Sayyid Abū al-Qāsim al-Khūʾī's Muʿjam Rijāl al-Ḥadīth)
  - Muʿjam al-Alf Rajul — Sayyid Ghayth Shubar
    (anchored in Sayyid Ḥusayn al-Burūjirdī's 12-generation ṭabaqāt system)
  - The Thaqalayn API hadith corpus (https://www.thaqalayn-api.net)

These works are public Shia scholarship distributed for educational and
research purposes. Computed values (tabaqah inferences, transmission
verdicts, chain grades) are produced by the software in this repository and
are clearly labeled as such; they do not represent the position of any
classical scholar and require human scholarly review.

The MIT license above applies to the SOFTWARE (Python code, configuration,
documentation). The DATA is redistributed under the principles of fair use
for Islamic scholarship. If you use the data in derivative work, please
preserve attribution to the original authors.
